<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">(Optional) Configure NFS Server</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 7 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><br>
</p><p>
This section describes how to manually configure NFS shares for CDF and the suite.&nbsp;</p><div class="Admonition_Note"><span class="autonumber">Note </span>Operations Bridge supports both EFS and NFS file systems. Skip this section and see <i>Amazon EFS</i> if you plan to use EFS file system.</div>
